  "description": "I want to start logging what media I engage with, and am curious about the best way to do that with GnoponEmacs. To start, I\u0026rsquo;m looking at what Org-roam Dailies are like. Checking the Org-roam Manual, it seems like they\u0026rsquo;re meant for one daily file per day, which isn\u0026rsquo;t quite what I\u0026rsquo;m picturing. A separate file for every media log entry seems like it\u0026rsquo;d cause bloat, but a single file might end up too long. I guess I could chunk them by month or year? But it sounds like for now the right move is to not worry more about it, make org/per/media-log.org, and a capture template at pm for entries, i.e. pmm for music.\n",
  "name": "2025-07-21, Recording my media consumption in gnoponemacs",
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Person",
